==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Turanian
<hw>Tu*ra"ni*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>pr. a.</pos> <ety>[From
<ets>Tur</ets>, the name, in Persian legendary history, of one of the
three brothers from whom sprang the races of mankind.]</ety> <def>Of,
pertaining to, or designating, an extensive family of languages of
simple structure and low grade (called also <stype>Altaic</stype>,
<stype>Ural-Altaic</stype>, and <stype>Scythian</stype>), spoken in the
northern parts of Europe and Asia and in Central Asia; of pertaining to,
or designating, the people who speak these languages.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Turanian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Turanian
<hw>Tu*ra"ni*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>pr. n.</pos> <def>One of the
Turanians.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

